WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:17.559
I'm really excited to be teaching a two-day workshop at the 2019 rStudio Conference on

00:00:17.559 --> 00:00:19.360
Shiny in Production.

00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:26.000
I'll be joined by a powerhouse of rStudio engineers and engineers outside of rStudio,

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:31.120
all of whom have a great background in building out awesome Shiny applications and scaling

00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:33.639
them in the enterprise in production.

00:00:33.639 --> 00:00:37.660
So I'm really looking forward to teaching this workshop, showing you some of the tips

00:00:37.660 --> 00:00:42.840
and tricks, as well as the processes and cultures that you can adopt to be successful bringing

00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:45.259
Shiny into production.

00:00:45.259 --> 00:00:50.000
And while pretty much everyone these days is learning how to write Shiny applications,

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:55.320
and there's tons of excellent material out there to teach you how to build beautiful,

00:00:55.320 --> 00:01:00.040
excellent Shiny applications that do meaningful things, there's a lot less information on

00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:05.839
how to deploy and scale and combat your IT department when they ask you, you know, who's

00:01:05.839 --> 00:01:10.680
going to ensure this application works at 2 a.m. in the morning when a thousand people

00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:11.680
are trying to visit it.

00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:13.919
So that's what this course is designed to address.

00:01:13.919 --> 00:01:19.639
We've spent almost a year building tools and processes to help you bring Shiny into production

00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:26.360
and to make sure that R and Shiny are first-class citizens in the enterprise architecture.

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:30.440
This course will cover all of those tools, as well as those processes and cultures.

00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:35.320
It'll teach you the language that DevOps teams expect you to be able to speak, and it'll

00:01:35.320 --> 00:01:40.559
show you by the end of the course how to approach the problem of bringing your Shiny application

00:01:40.559 --> 00:01:44.199
to hundreds or thousands of users.

00:01:44.199 --> 00:01:48.639
I'm really excited to see you all at rStudio conference.

00:01:48.639 --> 00:01:51.959
I'm looking forward to all the great talks that we have lined up.

00:01:51.959 --> 00:01:57.040
I know I'm going to learn a lot, both from my colleagues at rStudio and all of the great

00:01:57.040 --> 00:01:59.360
R users coming to the conference.

00:01:59.360 --> 00:02:01.519
I'm also really looking forward to teaching this class.

00:02:01.519 --> 00:02:06.879
It's going to be an excellent opportunity for all of us to come together, discuss and

00:02:06.879 --> 00:02:09.199
learn what Shiny in production really means.

00:02:09.199 --> 00:02:10.479
So I'm looking forward to seeing you.

00:02:10.479 --> 00:02:14.679
Check out our website to learn more about the conference and Shiny in production.

